1
00:00:12,666 --> 00:00:16,633
[theme music]

2
00:01:37,462 --> 00:01:42,928
-[gasping]

3
00:01:42,962 --> 00:01:44,128
-I understand.

4
00:01:44,162 --> 00:01:48,862
I can't be your boyfriend,
but I can act like it.

5
00:01:48,895 --> 00:01:52,328
-Thank you so much, I'll try
my hardest to make you love me.

6
00:01:52,362 --> 00:01:54,195
I promise.

7
00:01:54,228 --> 00:01:55,828
LIGHT (VOICEOVER):
I'll arrange for her

8
00:01:55,862 --> 00:01:58,062
to meet L. She'll
tell me his name,

9
00:01:58,095 --> 00:02:00,995
and then I eliminate
the entire task force.

10
00:02:01,028 --> 00:02:04,628
And when that's done,
I'll kill her, too.

11
00:02:04,662 --> 00:02:06,862
After all, she's
the only person who

12
00:02:06,895 --> 00:02:10,062
knows Kira's true
identity-- the only one.

13
00:02:10,095 --> 00:02:12,795
I can't let her
live much longer.

14
00:02:12,828 --> 00:02:15,062
-So you'll just pretend?

15
00:02:15,095 --> 00:02:15,795
All right.

16
00:02:15,828 --> 00:02:17,328
I guess it's a good start.

17
00:02:17,362 --> 00:02:19,228
Well, now that we
talked about that,

18
00:02:19,262 --> 00:02:20,828
could you show me
your Shinigami?

19
00:02:20,862 --> 00:02:21,895
I really want to see him.

20
00:02:21,928 --> 00:02:23,595
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): I
need her to trust me.

21
00:02:23,628 --> 00:02:25,328
I guess I have to.

22
00:02:25,362 --> 00:02:26,295
-Yeah, sure.

23
00:02:26,328 --> 00:02:28,362
Could you please turn around?

24
00:02:28,395 --> 00:02:29,062
MISA: All right.

25
00:02:36,528 --> 00:02:38,028
LIGHT: You can turn back now.

26
00:02:38,062 --> 00:02:40,762
MISA: OK.

27
00:02:40,795 --> 00:02:41,462
-Hey there.

28
00:02:41,495 --> 00:02:42,595
How's it going?

29
00:02:42,628 --> 00:02:44,095
MISA: Oh, look at that.

30
00:02:44,128 --> 00:02:46,528
You're a completely different
type of Shinigami than Rem,

31
00:02:46,562 --> 00:02:47,295
aren't you?

32
00:02:47,328 --> 00:02:48,328
I already know your name.

33
00:02:48,362 --> 00:02:49,128
It's Ryuk, right?

34
00:02:49,162 --> 00:02:50,895
Nice to meet you.

35
00:02:50,928 --> 00:02:51,395
-Yeah.

36
00:02:51,428 --> 00:02:52,662
Same here.

37
00:02:52,695 --> 00:02:54,528
MISA: Oh, and by the
way, Light, darling,

38
00:02:54,562 --> 00:02:56,528
do you know how to
kill a Shinigami?

39
00:02:56,562 --> 00:02:57,362
-Hm?

40
00:02:57,395 --> 00:02:59,462
Did you just call me darling?

41
00:02:59,495 --> 00:03:00,595
-Fine.

42
00:03:00,628 --> 00:03:02,595
Then do you mind if I
call you Knight instead?

43
00:03:02,628 --> 00:03:05,028
'Cause you're like my knight
in shining armor, you know.

44
00:03:05,062 --> 00:03:07,795
LIGHT: [sigh] Let's
just stick with Light.

45
00:03:07,828 --> 00:03:09,562
MAN: So, were you
actually planning

46
00:03:09,595 --> 00:03:12,562
to check all of the footage
we got from Aoyama on the 22nd

47
00:03:12,595 --> 00:03:13,562
by yourself?

48
00:03:13,595 --> 00:03:14,828
-That's right.

49
00:03:14,862 --> 00:03:16,862
I think it's very likely
that Kira and the second Kira

50
00:03:16,895 --> 00:03:19,162
make contact with each
other there on that day.

51
00:03:19,195 --> 00:03:21,762
So I want to check all of
these tapes personally.

52
00:03:21,795 --> 00:03:23,428
Also, Mr. Yagami?

53
00:03:23,462 --> 00:03:24,628
-Uh, yes?

54
00:03:24,662 --> 00:03:26,995
L: Please ask Mr. Mogi
to start following Light,

55
00:03:27,028 --> 00:03:28,928
so we can keep tabs
on what he's doing.

56
00:03:28,962 --> 00:03:30,895
YAGAMI: You want him followed?

57
00:03:30,928 --> 00:03:32,262
-It's only a slim chance.

58
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:34,628
But if you Light is Kira, then
there's still a possibility

59
00:03:34,662 --> 00:03:37,928
that the second Kira might
try to contact him somehow.

60
00:03:37,962 --> 00:03:38,428
-Mm.

61
00:03:38,462 --> 00:03:40,228
Very well

62
00:03:40,262 --> 00:03:42,728
-I'm starting to wonder
if Ryuzaki is even human.

63
00:03:42,762 --> 00:03:44,095
The guy never sleeps.

64
00:03:44,128 --> 00:03:46,428
-I saw him sleeping in
that exact same position

65
00:03:46,462 --> 00:03:47,495
the other day.

66
00:03:47,528 --> 00:03:48,295
-Huh.

67
00:03:48,328 --> 00:03:49,462
MAN: No, I'm serious.

68
00:03:53,295 --> 00:03:56,762
LIGHT: So if a Shinigami has
feelings for a human and kills

69
00:03:56,795 --> 00:03:59,162
someone else in order to
extend that human's life

70
00:03:59,195 --> 00:04:02,662
beyond its natural end,
and Shinigami will die?

71
00:04:02,695 --> 00:04:04,462
-That's right.

72
00:04:04,495 --> 00:04:06,928
--[laughs] Good luck
trying to find a Shinigami

73
00:04:06,962 --> 00:04:08,528
who'd volunteer to do that?

74
00:04:08,562 --> 00:04:10,528
-[laugh] That's true.

75
00:04:10,562 --> 00:04:13,128
I can't see you ever doing that.

76
00:04:13,162 --> 00:04:16,062
By the way, where did you
send all those tapes from,

77
00:04:16,095 --> 00:04:17,662
the ones that went
to the TV stations?

78
00:04:17,695 --> 00:04:18,862
-Let's see.

79
00:04:18,895 --> 00:04:22,562
Osaka the first time,
then Tokyo, this other one

80
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:23,928
from Nagano.

81
00:04:23,962 --> 00:04:25,995
I took the bullet train every
time, so that way the police

82
00:04:26,028 --> 00:04:27,795
couldn't pinpoint my location.

83
00:04:27,828 --> 00:04:28,562
-All right.

84
00:04:28,595 --> 00:04:29,695
One more thing.

85
00:04:29,728 --> 00:04:31,528
Do you still have the
videotapes and envelopes

86
00:04:31,562 --> 00:04:33,362
with your friends
fingerprints on them?

87
00:04:33,395 --> 00:04:34,495
-Uh-huh.

88
00:04:34,528 --> 00:04:35,728
-Well, you'll have to
dispose of everything

89
00:04:35,762 --> 00:04:37,495
that was used to create
those videotapes.

90
00:04:37,528 --> 00:04:38,795
Understand?

91
00:04:38,828 --> 00:04:42,195
But before you do, I need
you to send one last video,

92
00:04:42,228 --> 00:04:44,728
and make sure it's from a
place you haven't used yet.

93
00:04:44,762 --> 00:04:49,895
It should say, "I've decided
to stop searching for Kira.

94
00:04:49,928 --> 00:04:51,862
And I'd like to thank
the police department

95
00:04:51,895 --> 00:04:53,528
for all of its advice.

96
00:04:53,562 --> 00:04:57,462
However, I still plan to
help Kira in his mission,

97
00:04:57,495 --> 00:05:01,462
and I hope that in time he
will come to see me an ally.

98
00:05:01,495 --> 00:05:03,428
I will start by
punishing criminals

99
00:05:03,462 --> 00:05:05,695
that Kira has yet to judge.

100
00:05:05,728 --> 00:05:10,895
Also, I will share my power with
others who I feel are worthy.

101
00:05:10,928 --> 00:05:13,162
And I will encourage
them to do the same.

102
00:05:13,195 --> 00:05:15,495
Together, we'll make this
world a better place."

103
00:05:15,528 --> 00:05:17,128
MISA: Share my power?

104
00:05:17,162 --> 00:05:20,028
-We'll just add that part to
throw off their investigation.

105
00:05:20,062 --> 00:05:21,462
They suspect that
there are already

106
00:05:21,495 --> 00:05:23,795
two people with this power,
so it wouldn't be a stretch

107
00:05:23,828 --> 00:05:25,195
to assume there could be others.

108
00:05:25,228 --> 00:05:27,028
And if they believe the
numbers are growing,

109
00:05:27,062 --> 00:05:28,295
then they'll start to panic.

110
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:29,495
Can you do this?

111
00:05:29,528 --> 00:05:30,562
-No need to ask.

112
00:05:30,595 --> 00:05:32,695
Just tell me what to
do, and I'll do it.

113
00:05:32,728 --> 00:05:35,028
I don't care what it is,
'cause I'd do anything for you.

114
00:05:35,062 --> 00:05:37,328
LIGHT: There's one more thing,
which is very important.

115
00:05:37,362 --> 00:05:38,295
-What's that?

116
00:05:38,328 --> 00:05:41,062
-If you get arrested
by the police,

117
00:05:41,095 --> 00:05:43,195
or if you're ever brought
in for questioning,

118
00:05:43,228 --> 00:05:46,795
you can never mention anything
about us or the Death Note.

119
00:05:46,828 --> 00:05:48,895
As long as they don't get
a hold of that notebook,

120
00:05:48,928 --> 00:05:51,428
there's no proof that
you did anything.

121
00:05:51,462 --> 00:05:53,628
Can you promise to say nothing?

122
00:05:53,662 --> 00:05:54,795
-I promise.

123
00:05:54,828 --> 00:05:56,995
So this must mean
that we're officially

124
00:05:57,028 --> 00:05:58,828
boyfriend and girlfriend
now, aren't we?

125
00:05:58,862 --> 00:05:59,462
-Well sure.

126
00:05:59,495 --> 00:06:00,562
I guess.

127
00:06:00,595 --> 00:06:02,762
MISA: Then I'd like
to add one condition.

128
00:06:02,795 --> 00:06:05,595
You have to go on a date
with me at least once week.

129
00:06:05,628 --> 00:06:06,395
-[sigh]

130
00:06:06,428 --> 00:06:07,628
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): Unbelievable.

131
00:06:07,662 --> 00:06:09,028
She still doesn't get it.

132
00:06:09,062 --> 00:06:09,862
-We can't.

133
00:06:09,895 --> 00:06:11,895
-[gasp] But why?

134
00:06:11,928 --> 00:06:14,362
-It looks like I'm going to
have to spell this out for you.

135
00:06:14,395 --> 00:06:16,262
L already suspects
that I'm Kira.

136
00:06:16,295 --> 00:06:18,128
Do you see what I'm saying here?

137
00:06:18,162 --> 00:06:19,062
-No way.

138
00:06:19,095 --> 00:06:20,895
L is amazing.

139
00:06:20,928 --> 00:06:23,962
I mean, everyone's been saying
that he's getting nowhere

140
00:06:23,995 --> 00:06:25,462
with the investigation
and that he's

141
00:06:25,495 --> 00:06:26,795
a complete idiot and stuff.

142
00:06:26,828 --> 00:06:28,795
But he already knows that much?

143
00:06:28,828 --> 00:06:30,128
-Anyway.

144
00:06:30,162 --> 00:06:32,162
It's all worked out well for
me, because thanks to that,

145
00:06:32,195 --> 00:06:34,662
I've also been able
to get close to L.

146
00:06:34,695 --> 00:06:35,662
-Huh?

147
00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:37,628
You and L are in
contact with each other?

148
00:06:37,662 --> 00:06:39,495
Then that's even more amazing.

149
00:06:39,528 --> 00:06:42,228
This is getting so exciting!

150
00:06:42,262 --> 00:06:43,762
-Even though he
suspects I'm Kira,

151
00:06:43,795 --> 00:06:46,928
L figures he's safe as long
as I don't know his real name.

152
00:06:46,962 --> 00:06:51,195
He came right out and told me
who we was, just to get to me.

153
00:06:51,228 --> 00:06:53,828
However, he's only
focusing on me

154
00:06:53,862 --> 00:06:55,395
because he has no
other suspects.

155
00:06:55,428 --> 00:06:58,528
And he has no evidence.

156
00:06:58,562 --> 00:07:01,628
At this moment, I'm working
with him on the case.

157
00:07:01,662 --> 00:07:04,562
And little by little,
I'm winning his trust.

158
00:07:04,595 --> 00:07:05,428
-Great.

159
00:07:05,462 --> 00:07:06,828
So I'll you have
to do is take me

160
00:07:06,862 --> 00:07:09,028
to where L is and I can
see his real name for you.

161
00:07:09,062 --> 00:07:11,128
LIGHT: I'm afraid
it's not that simple.

162
00:07:11,162 --> 00:07:12,162
-Hm?

163
00:07:12,195 --> 00:07:13,228
LIGHT: Listen, it
was difficult enough

164
00:07:13,262 --> 00:07:15,262
for me to get close to him.

165
00:07:15,295 --> 00:07:18,295
Besides, if all of a
sudden someone I just met

166
00:07:18,328 --> 00:07:19,828
gets too close, and
at the same time,

167
00:07:19,862 --> 00:07:21,495
the police detect
changes in Kira

168
00:07:21,528 --> 00:07:24,362
or the second Kira's
behavior, that person

169
00:07:24,395 --> 00:07:26,295
will be suspected of
being in the second Kira.

170
00:07:26,328 --> 00:07:30,128
And of course, that'll put me
under even greater suspicion.

171
00:07:30,162 --> 00:07:32,328
We can't allow them to
make that connection, which

172
00:07:32,362 --> 00:07:35,495
means we can't appear to
be too close to each other.

173
00:07:35,528 --> 00:07:37,795
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

174
00:07:37,828 --> 00:07:40,528
-Well, I think I understand.

175
00:07:40,562 --> 00:07:42,428
So is that why we
can't go on dates?

176
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:44,395
We can't be seen in
public, because it'll

177
00:07:44,428 --> 00:07:45,395
look too suspicious?

178
00:07:45,428 --> 00:07:48,062
-Look, we need to
take the time now

179
00:07:48,095 --> 00:07:49,995
to come up with a
good plan, some way

180
00:07:50,028 --> 00:07:53,162
that you can see L without
letting him know you exist.

181
00:07:53,195 --> 00:07:54,128
-Yeah.

182
00:07:54,162 --> 00:07:56,062
LIGHT: I can't
eliminate L without you,

183
00:07:56,095 --> 00:07:59,862
so I'll call you and see you as
often as this situation allows?

184
00:07:59,895 --> 00:08:01,162
-You will.

185
00:08:01,195 --> 00:08:01,662
-But--

186
00:08:01,695 --> 00:08:02,862
-Oh?

187
00:08:02,895 --> 00:08:04,828
- --to make sure that our
meetings to stand out,

188
00:08:04,862 --> 00:08:08,228
I have to make sure that I'm
seen with other girls, OK?

189
00:08:08,262 --> 00:08:08,828
MISA: Huh?

190
00:08:08,862 --> 00:08:09,895
What do you mean?

191
00:08:09,928 --> 00:08:12,328
You're seriously gonna
date other girls?

192
00:08:12,362 --> 00:08:13,228
-Yeah, more or less.

193
00:08:13,262 --> 00:08:14,995
-I don't want you too!

194
00:08:15,028 --> 00:08:16,962
-Huh?

195
00:08:16,995 --> 00:08:20,862
-If I see you with another
girl, I'll kill her.

196
00:08:20,895 --> 00:08:22,662
-Scary.

197
00:08:22,695 --> 00:08:24,495
-Look, sweetie.

198
00:08:24,528 --> 00:08:26,428
-Sweetie? [laughs]

199
00:08:26,462 --> 00:08:27,995
-This is not a game.

200
00:08:28,028 --> 00:08:31,628
Both of us are risking our lives
to change the world, aren't we?

201
00:08:31,662 --> 00:08:33,295
-I know that.

202
00:08:33,328 --> 00:08:36,862
But I love you more
than the world, Light.

203
00:08:36,895 --> 00:08:38,562
-It sounds like you're confused.

204
00:08:38,595 --> 00:08:40,828
Maybe it feels that way
to you, but you're here

205
00:08:40,862 --> 00:08:42,595
because you admire Kira.

206
00:08:42,628 --> 00:08:44,128
You don't even know me.

207
00:08:44,162 --> 00:08:45,495
We just met.

208
00:08:45,528 --> 00:08:47,795
-Don't you believe in
love at first sight?

209
00:08:47,828 --> 00:08:48,862
-No.

210
00:08:48,895 --> 00:08:51,062
-I admit that everything
you said was true.

211
00:08:51,095 --> 00:08:54,162
I did want to meet Kira out
of gratitude and respect,

212
00:08:54,195 --> 00:08:55,295
not love.

213
00:08:55,328 --> 00:08:58,062
But from the moment I
first saw you, I knew.

214
00:08:58,095 --> 00:09:00,395
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): What
is wrong with this girl?

215
00:09:00,428 --> 00:09:03,195
-Popular, as always.

216
00:09:03,228 --> 00:09:06,795
-Well, you can show me
your love by obeying me.

217
00:09:06,828 --> 00:09:09,262
I thought you said it
was OK if I used you.

218
00:09:09,295 --> 00:09:11,695
A minute ago, you swore
you'd do anything I asked.

219
00:09:11,728 --> 00:09:12,795
-Yeah, I did.

220
00:09:12,828 --> 00:09:15,095
But I never said you
could date other girls.

221
00:09:15,128 --> 00:09:18,495
I mean, those are two
totally different things.

222
00:09:18,528 --> 00:09:21,762
-I think you're forgetting
I have both notebooks.

223
00:09:21,795 --> 00:09:24,528
If you don't obey me,
I can easily kill you.

224
00:09:24,562 --> 00:09:29,095
-I would never allow
that, Light Yagami.

225
00:09:29,128 --> 00:09:32,595
If you do anything that
results in this girl's death,

226
00:09:32,628 --> 00:09:35,862
the first thing I'll do is right
your name in my Death Note.

227
00:09:35,895 --> 00:09:38,895
I will kill you.

228
00:09:38,928 --> 00:09:43,028
I'm sure you realize that
I can see her life span.

229
00:09:43,062 --> 00:09:45,528
If she happens to
die before that time,

230
00:09:45,562 --> 00:09:48,395
I'll know it was
you who killed her.

231
00:09:48,428 --> 00:09:50,795
LIGHT: But if you were to use
your Death Note to save her,

232
00:09:50,828 --> 00:09:52,728
wouldn't that mean
you'd die, too?

233
00:09:52,762 --> 00:09:53,828
-That's right.

234
00:09:53,862 --> 00:09:56,362
If you tried to save
me, you would die, too.

235
00:09:56,395 --> 00:09:58,462
-Yes, you are correct.

236
00:09:58,495 --> 00:10:03,062
But I'm quite willing
to accept that outcome.

237
00:10:03,095 --> 00:10:04,895
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): Is
this Shinigami serious?

238
00:10:04,928 --> 00:10:05,628
This is crazy.

239
00:10:05,662 --> 00:10:06,795
Then this means--

240
00:10:06,828 --> 00:10:07,728
[knocking]

241
00:10:07,762 --> 00:10:08,428
LIGHT (VOICEOVER):
--from now on--

242
00:10:08,462 --> 00:10:09,095
LIGHT'S MOTHER: Light?

243
00:10:09,128 --> 00:10:10,395
-Huh?

244
00:10:10,428 --> 00:10:13,162
Yeah, what is it?

245
00:10:13,195 --> 00:10:15,428
-It's almost 11:30, you know.

246
00:10:15,462 --> 00:10:18,162
You really shouldn't have
a girl here this late.

247
00:10:18,195 --> 00:10:19,662
-Oh, of course.

248
00:10:19,695 --> 00:10:21,728
I guess we lost track of time.

249
00:10:21,762 --> 00:10:22,895
MISA: Sorry, Mrs. Yagami.

250
00:10:25,895 --> 00:10:29,195
I'm really sorry for coming
over so late at night.

251
00:10:29,228 --> 00:10:30,895
See you later, Light.

252
00:10:30,928 --> 00:10:31,995
-Yeah.

253
00:10:32,028 --> 00:10:34,328
-Light, you should walk
her to the station.

